race.description: Greyhounds As Pets Mixed Stake Ctb Division1
race.comment: JOSIE DAKOTA (1) charged out of the boxes with a slick early split and went straight to the front, scoring an all the way win (30.83) over 531m at Gawler. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Great chance again. SLICK ANGEL (3) was the fastest winner on the program last time out, running away to score by 0.8 lengths (30.89) at Gawler. Harder here but expected to feature again. BOOM BOOM JACK (8) is an honest type in the frame at 26 of 56 starts including last time when second (31.28) over 531m at Gawler. Form here sound including five wins. Looks suited and expected to run well. FERRERO GIRL (2) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot from this box most recently.
